[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    326[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m##[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mThe AWS Implementation[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    327[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    328[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;143;161;179m###[38;2;192;197;206m [38;2;143;161;179mWhy These Services[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    329[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    330[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mAmazon SageMaker for the model training and serving stack.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m Three model families live here: the per-gap-type clinical urgency model (gradient-boosted regression, optionally with a supervised outcome layer for gaps with rich training data), the per-pathway engagement and completion-probability models (gradient-boosted binary classifiers, one per pathway), and an optional per-gap-type uplift model where randomized closure-pathway data exists. The recommendation run uses SageMaker Batch Transform; same reasoning as 4.4 and 4.5 (batch is dramatically cheaper than an idle real-time endpoint, and gap evaluation runs are scheduled). Visit-context ranking runs on a near-real-time cadence (the day before each visit); it can use the offline-trained models with cached scores rather than requiring a live endpoint. SageMaker is HIPAA-eligible under BAA. [38;2;101;115;126m<!--[38;2;101;115;126m TODO: confirm SageMaker Batch Transform's current HIPAA eligibility and the appropriate instance types for the model sizes implied here. [38;2;101;115;126m-->[K
