[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1424[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1425[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mWhere it struggles:[38;2;235;203;139m**[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1426[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1427[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPatients with fragmented care across multiple practices.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A patient who sees PCPs in two different health systems and gets screened at retail clinics has gap closure events scattered across data sources the recommender doesn't all see. The [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mdata_quality_flag[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m exposes this, but downstream consumers (chase team, dashboards) need to gate on it. A "gap open" label on a patient with [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcross_provider_fragmentation[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m data quality is much less reliable than the same label on a patient with [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mcomplete[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m data quality.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1428[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mNewly attributed patients.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m A patient who joined the plan or attributed to the practice within the last 60 days has minimal historical data for engagement and closure-probability prediction. Cold-start cohort defaults are essential, and the recommender should weight patient-specific predictions less heavily for these patients until enough history accumulates.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1429[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mMeasures with ambiguous numerator definitions.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some measure specifications have been written in ways that admit multiple interpretations. Different vendors' implementations of the "same" HEDIS measure can produce different numerators by 1 to 3 percentage points. The recipe's measure registry encodes one interpretation; reconciling with the plan's PBM/HEDIS-vendor numerators requires explicit alignment work and ongoing comparison.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1430[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mSpecialty-care gap closures.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Gaps that close via specialist visits (retinal exam, mammogram, colonoscopy) depend on the specialist documenting and the data flowing back to the PCP's view. A patient who had the colonoscopy at a specialist not in the plan's data exchange may show as "open" indefinitely. Patient self-report is a partial mitigation; dedicated data-exchange agreements with frequent-referral specialists are the durable fix.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1431[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mMeasures where the PCP can't drive closure.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some gap closures are entirely outside the PCP's control: a follow-up after a hospitalization for mental illness (HEDIS FUH) requires the patient to attend a follow-up encounter; the PCP can flag, refer, and remind but cannot force the appointment. The recommender should not surface these as in-visit agenda items for the PCP except as awareness; they belong in the chase-team queue.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1432[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mCohort fairness in the urgency model.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m If the training data has systematically different follow-up rates by demographic cohort, the urgency model will be miscalibrated by cohort, with higher uncertainty for under-followed groups. Cohort-aware calibration and ongoing fairness monitoring are not nice-to-haves.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1433[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mWindow-driven prioritization swamping clinical urgency.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m As measure-year ends approach, the window-urgency term in the priority synthesis grows, and operationally-attractive but clinically-low-urgency gaps can swamp the top of the priority-sorted list. The policy weights need a hard cap on how much window urgency can dominate; otherwise the David scenario from The Problem section recurs at scale every December.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1434[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mPatient-driven home test kits with low completion rates.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m FIT kits, A1c home kits, and similar self-administered tests have meaningful completion rates only when the kit is followed by reminders and tied to a clear result-return process. A kit-fulfillment record is not a closure; the result return is the closure. Track both, and don't credit the kit-send as a closure.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1435[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mClinicians who systematically override.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Some PCPs override most agenda items because they distrust the recommender (or because they prefer to drive their own visit agenda). The retraining loop should treat overrides as signal carefully: a per-PCP override-rate filter prevents the model from down-weighting recommendations to that PCP's patients globally based on their override pattern. Per-recommendation reasons matter; per-PCP attitudes don't.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    1436[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [K
